The two primary sites for Crohn’s disease are the ileum, which is the last portion of the small bowel (ileitis, regional enteritis), and the colon (Crohn’s colitis).
Psyllium maintains remission in ulcerative colitis.
Dietary fiber maintains remission in human ulcerative colitis, an effect related with an increased Luminal production of short-chain fatty acids (SCFA).
Dietary fiber Supplementation ameliorated colonic damage in HLA-B2712.
